  <div class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2">UrbanAccess: Navigating the City Without Limits</div>
  <div class="w-full" style="margin-top: 0px; text-align: justify;">
    <p>
      People with disabilities face significant challenges navigating cities due to lack of real-time, reliable accessibility information and unforeseen obstacles in infrastructure.
	  </br></br>
	  UrbanAccess is an innovative mobile navigation app designed for people with disabilities. It provides real-time, reliable, and personalized accessibility information for urban environments. Using crowdsourced data, AI-powered mapping, and augmented reality (AR), the app enables users to plan accessible routes, receive live updates on obstacles, and rate public facilities based on inclusivity. Advanced machine learning techniques are used for pavement distress identification, stair detection, and obstacle recognition, ensuring precise and up-to-date accessibility insights. Additionally, the augmented reality feature enhances accessibility by providing audio cues, haptic feedback, and visual contrast adjustments, helping partially sighted users navigate urban environments more effectively. Beyond improving mobility and independence for individuals, UrbanAccess also provides valuable data-driven insights for city planners and businesses to create more inclusive spaces.
	  </br></br>
	  This concept was developed as part of the <a href="https://www.imperialenterpriselab.com/programmes/global-challenge-lab/" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"> Global Challenge Lab 2024</a>, an international innovation program hosted in the UK by Imperial College London’s Enterprise Lab.
    </p>
  </div>

