  <div class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2">M³: Math Without Borders</div>
  <div class="w-full" style="margin-top: 0px; text-align: justify;">
    <p>
      Current math education relies heavily on language, making it inaccessible to children who do not understand the language of instruction. This issue affects underserved communities, leaving children struggling with both linguistic and mathematical barriers and widening global education inequalities.
	  </br></br>
	  M Cubed (M³) addresses this challenge with an AI-powered, language-free math learning platform that teaches foundational and advanced math concepts using visual, culturally neutral content. Unlike traditional methods, M Cubed eliminates the need for text-based explanations, ensuring that children, regardless of their language background, can develop problem-solving skills and mathematical proficiency. The platform features AI-driven personalized learning, gamified interactive exercises, and offline functionality, making it accessible even in low-connectivity regions. By removing language as a barrier, M Cubed empowers children worldwide with equal opportunities to learn and succeed in mathematics.
	  </br></br>
	  This concept was developed as part of the <a href="https://www.hultprize.org/" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"> Hult Prize 2025</a> competition, a global initiative that empowers young entrepreneurs to create innovative, impact-driven solutions to social challenges that aligns to the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). 
    </p>
